ontent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gaz1665702569498.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gaz1665702569498.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gaz1665702569498.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gaz1665702569498\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Strip end-of-line character from empty input file when <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">fileload</span> or\n      <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">lfileload</span> is used.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"gaz1665702569498__topic_d140435e1_d140436e1_d140437e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gaz1665702569498__p_d140438e1_d140439e1_d140440e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$FILELOAD_SINGLE_LINE</span> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>} <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gaz1665702569498__section_s1j_q2x_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d943624e74\">Defaults </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"gaz1665702569498__table_d16646e1_d16647e1_d16648e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Client assignment files </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Section: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[SETTINGS] </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Default value: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">None </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gaz1665702569498__section_pc4_q2x_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d943624e120\">Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gaz1665702569498__p_d140447e1_d140448e1_d140449e1\">When <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$FILELOAD_SINGLE_LINE</span> is set\n        to <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">fileload</span> or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">lfileload</span> will\n        strip the end-of-line character from an otherwise empty input file, so the resulting data is\n        truly empty.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rxb1665702568451.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>fileload</a><p>Copy the contents of a file into a field or variable.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cnw1665702572057.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>lfileload</a><p>Copy the contents of a file into a field or variable, ignoring any file redirections in the assignment file.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527776\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527776\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$FILELOAD_SINGLE_LINE Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 30, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Strip end-of-line character from empty input file when fileload or lfileload is used. $FILELOAD_SINGLE_LINE { = } 1 | 0 Defaults Assignment file: Client assignment files Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: None Description When $FILELOAD_SINGLE_LINE is set to 1 , fileload or lfileload will strip the end-of-line character from an otherwise empty input file, so the resulting data is truly empty. Related Links fileload Copy the contents of a file into a field or variable. lfileload Copy the contents of a file into a field or variable, ignoring any file redirections in the assignment file. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}